POC2 - Quick assessment of FilterLabs.ai Org List

This document provides a brief query of organizations found the FilterLabs.ai organization list (August, 2003). Sets of key words are separated using the vertical slash. Counts, bounding boxes, and lists of associated orgs are provided for each set of search terms.

## Global options
knitr::opts_chunk$set(cache = FALSE)
pacman::p_load(tidyverse, sf, rmarkdown, usmap)

map_dat <- st_as_sf(maps::map("state", fill=TRUE, plot =FALSE)) |> filter(ID %in% c('arizona','utah','washington','idaho','montana','california','nevada','colorado','new mexico','oregon','wyoming')) 

dat <- read.csv('rmd/poc2_filterlabs_orglist/BILPOC2_GROUPS-Aug.csv') |>
  mutate(name = tolower(Name)) |>
  mutate(bbox = paste0('(',NE_LAT,',',NE_LNG,',',SW_LAT,',',SW_LNG,')'))

search <- function(txt) {
  
    cat('\n\n## Search terms', cnt, '\n')
    cat('<span style = "color:blue">', gsub('\\|', ' || ', txt), '</span>\n\n')
    
    dat_s <- dat |> filter(grepl(txt, name)) 
    cat(paste('Organization count =', nrow(dat_s), '\n'))
      
    p1 <- 
      ggplot() + 
      geom_sf(data = map_dat) +
      geom_rect(
        data = dat_s,
        aes(xmin = SW_LNG, xmax = NE_LNG, ymin = NE_LAT, ymax = SW_LAT), 
        fill=NA, color='black') +
      coord_sf(xlim = c(-125, -102), ylim = c(32, 49))
    
    suppressWarnings( {
        print(p1)
    })

  cnt <<- cnt + 1
} 

search_table <- function(txt){
  
  dat_s <- dat |> filter(grepl(txt, name)) 
  DT::datatable(dat_s |> select(Name, Audience.Location))
  
}
